@startuml project-journey
!theme plain
skinparam backgroundColor white
skinparam activityBorderColor #333333
skinparam activityBackgroundColor #E8F4FD
skinparam activityDiamondBackgroundColor #FFF3CD
skinparam activityDiamondBorderColor #333333
skinparam arrowColor #333333
skinparam noteBackgroundColor #F8F9FA

title GlowPowerRental SDLC - Project Journey

|Kickoff|
start
:Complete Project Kickoff Checklist
-- Sponsor identified
-- Team assigned
-- Repository created
-- Communication channel established;

|Phase 1: Business Analysis|
:Step 1: Conduct Business Needs Analysis
<i>(5 days)</i>
→ Problem Statement;
note right: Runbook: RB-P1-001

:Step 2: Develop Business Case
<i>(10 days)</i>
→ Business Case, Risk Register, KPIs;
note right: Runbook: RB-P1-002

:Step 3: Identify Stakeholders
<i>(3 days)</i>
→ Stakeholder Register;
note right: Runbook: RB-P1-004

:Step 4: Create Project Charter
<i>(5 days)</i>
→ Project Charter, RACI, Milestones;
note right: Runbook: RB-P1-003

if (Gate Review\nSponsor + Product Owner) then (Proceed)
else (Rework / Stop)
  :Return to relevant step;
  stop
endif

|Phase 2: Requirements Engineering|
:Step 5: Conduct Stakeholder Analysis
<i>(5 days)</i>
→ Refined Register, Comms Plan;
note right: Runbook: RB-P2-001

:Step 6: Extract Business Requirements
<i>(15 days)</i>
→ BRD (baselined);
note right: Runbook: RB-P2-002

:Step 7: Derive Software Requirements
<i>(5 days)</i>
→ SRS;
note right: Runbook: RB-P2-003

:Step 8: Validate & Baseline Requirements
→ RTM, Validation Report;
note right: Runbook: RB-P2-004

if (Gate Review\nPO + BA + Tech Lead + Domain Expert) then (Proceed)
else (Rework / Stop)
  :Return to relevant step;
  stop
endif

|Phase 3: System Architecture|
:Step 9: Create Architecture Description
<i>(15 days)</i>
→ ADD (ISO 42010 viewpoints)
→ ADRs
→ PlantUML diagrams:
  system-context, component,
  sequence, deployment, ERD, state;
note right: Runbook: RB-P3-001

if (Gate Review\nTech Lead + PO + QA Lead) then (Proceed)
else (Rework / Stop)
  :Return to relevant step;
  stop
endif

|Phase 4: Design|
:Step 10: Create Detailed Design
<i>(10 days)</i>
→ DDD, API Specs, Data Model
→ PlantUML diagrams:
  class, API flow, data flow;
note right: Runbook: RB-P4-001

if (Gate Review\nTech Lead + Developers) then (Proceed)
else (Rework / Stop)
  :Return to relevant step;
  stop
endif

|Phase 5: Development|
:Step 11: Implement Features (TDD)
<i>(variable)</i>
→ Source Code, Unit Tests
→ PRs using PR template
→ Code Review Records;
note right: Runbook: RB-P5-001

if (Gate Review\nTech Lead + QA Lead) then (Proceed)
else (Rework / Stop)
  :Return to relevant step;
  stop
endif

|Phase 6: Testing|
:Step 12: Execute Test Cycle
<i>(variable)</i>
→ Test Plan, Test Cases
→ Defect Reports
→ Test Summary Report
→ UAT Sign-Off;
note right: Runbook: RB-P6-001

if (Gate Review\nPO + Tech Lead + QA Lead) then (Proceed)
else (Rework / Stop)
  :Return to relevant step;
  stop
endif

|Deployment|
:Phase 7: Deploy to Production;
stop

@enduml
